  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:26:59.225174+00:00",
  "text": "Users should be able to use any variables names they like or using built-in keywords should throw an error while compiling\n\n### Version\r\n3.2.23\r\n\r\n### Reproduction link\r\n[sfc.vuejs.org/](https://sfc.vuejs.org/#)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\nSee the link above\r\n\r\n### What is expected?\r\nUser should be able to use `_createElementVNode` as it's desired variable name or compiler should give out an error during compile.\r\n\r\n### What is actually happening?\r\nRuntime gives out an error says `_createElementVNode is not a function`\r\n\r\n<!-- generated by vue-issues. DO NOT REMOVE -->",
